<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRAINING SET FOR PARK VOLUNTEERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Manhattan Beach Recreation Department will hold training sessions for 
volunteers interested in conducting nature study tours of the Polliwog Park 
pond, which was recently refurbished as a habitat for migratory water fowl. 
</P>
<P>
Sessions will be held from 7 to 9 p.m. on four consecutive Wednesdays, starting 
next week, at Manhattan Heights Community Center, 1600 Manhattan Beach Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
Tour guides will learn how to identify migratory birds and their eggs, other 
types of wildlife, and various plants and trees. The first free public nature 
study tour at Polliwog will be April 7 at 10 a.m. Volunteers may call 545-5621, 
Ext. 330, for further information. 
</P>
</TEXT>
