<P>
TUSTIN UPSET BY TORRANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STUART MATTHEWS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TUSTIN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Freshman guard Lisa Misipeka came off the bench to score 14 points in the 
fourth quarter, leading Torrance High School to a 55-52 upset over Tustin in 
the first round of the Southern Section 4-AA girls' playoffs Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
Tustin (21-6 overall and unbeaten in the Sea View League) led by as many as 10 
points in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
Torrance (16-10) took its first lead, 31-29, with 2:01 left in the third 
quarter. The teams then exchanged leads until Tustin's Shari Needham made a 
three-point basket to cut Torrance's advantage to 53-52 with 52 seconds left. 
</P>
<P>
But Tiffany Fujimoto then made two free throws to put the game away. 
</P>
<P>
Torrance, an at-large entry in the playoffs, was led by Misipeka, who had 15 
points and seven rebounds, and Fujimoto, who led all scorers with 20. 
</P>
<P>
Wanda Sequiera and Jennifer Coombs led Tustin with 12 points apiece. Nancy Vinh 
added 10, and Needham had nine. 
</P>
<P>
Tustin's Christine Garner, who entered the game averaging 16 points a game, 
scored eight points in the first half. But Torrance held her scoreless after 
that. STUART MATTHEWS 
</P>
</TEXT>
