<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GM Hughes Electronics Corp.: The diversified automotive, defense and space 
electronics firm's 1989 net income fell 3% from a year earlier to $781.2 
million. 
</P>
<P>
Revenue totaled a record $11.2 billion, up 2%. In the fourth quarter, the 
Detroit firm posted record earnings of $183 million, a gain of 8%. Revenue 
totaled $2.9 billion, off 6%. The results were attributed to a one-time charge 
for costs associated with an employee separation and early retirement plan at 
Hughes Aircraft Co. that reduced its total employment by 12%. 
</P>
</TEXT>
