</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fremont General Corp: The Santa Monica-based insurance and financial services 
company said its 1989 income rose 16% from 1988 to $17.6 million on revenue of 
$466.5 million, up 18%. Fourth-quarter net income soared to $9.49 million from 
$465,000 a year ago, as revenue climbed 30% to $127.2 million. The firm singled 
out a strong performance by its workers' compensation insurance companies and 
its $1-billion investment portfolio. 1989 earnings would have been 
significantly higher except for a second-quarter provision of $11.3 million to 
cover potential losses on loans in the Fremont Financial Corp. subsidiary. 
