<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: STAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Noble Gets the Nod: Adrian Noble, the 39-year-old director whose credits range 
from Shakespeare to Cole Porter, was named the next artistic director of Great 
Britain's Royal Shakespeare Company on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Noble will assume his post April 1 as artistic director-elect. He takes over 
fully in July, 1991, when current artistic director Terry Hands steps down 
after 25 years with the company. The announcement came just a week after the 
company announced it was closing its two London theaters this fall. BETH KLEID 
</P>
