<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: ALHAMBRA; 
</P>
<P>
2 FINANCIAL MOVES OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
To pay off existing debt and help finance development projects, the Alhambra 
Redevelopment Agency and the City Council have approved two bond issues. 
</P>
<P>
One of the new issues is a $3.4-million tax-exempt note, part of which the 
agency will use to pay $3.1 million it owes the city. The second is a 
$2.5-million taxable note to cover cost overruns and other redevelopment costs 
on agency projects. Annual payments on the two notes total $413,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
