</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOWELL ANDREWS, CIVIC LEADER, DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lowell A. Andrews, a longtime Glendora civic leader and 1986 Citizen of the 
Year, died Monday. 
</P>
<P>
He was 82. 
</P>
<P>
He was retired from the U.S. Forest Service, where he specialized in watershed 
management. A resident of Glendora for 54 years, he was president of the 
Kiwanis Club and had served as director of the Chamber of Commerce, the 
Foothill Presbyterian Hospital Foundation and the Glendora Coordinating 
Council. 
</P>
<P>
He is survived by his wife, Betty; one daughter, Sheryl Ogilvie; one son, Gary 
Andrews; a sister, Elsie White, and brother, Ed Andrews, both of Kansas; three 
grandchildren, and four great-grandchildren. 
</P>
<P>
A memorial service will be held at 3 p.m. Friday at Oakdale Memorial Park in 
Glendora. 
</P>
</TEXT>
