<HEADLINE>
<P>
HERE'S HOW AREA TEAMS STAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A look at how the Long Beach-Southeast area high school teams are doing in the 
Southern Section basketball playoffs, played Tuesday night. Second-round games 
are Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
In 5-AA, top-ranked Lynwood (27-1) got 36 points from Earnest Killum and 
defeated Arcadia, 104-72. The Knights will play at Alhambra (20-5) in the 
second round. 
</P>
<P>
Dante Powell scored 23 points to lead Millikan (20-7) to an 88-73 victory over 
Hemet. The Rams will play host to Saddleback (17-11) Friday in a rematch of 
last year's championship game. 
</P>
<P>
Poly (22-2) defeated Santa Monica, 71-52, as Rod Hannibal scored 18 points. 
Poly advances to play at Eisenhower (18-9). 
</P>
<P>
Center Terrence O'Kelley scored 25 points to lead Lakewood (16-10) over 
Palmdale, 69-61. The Lancers will play at Leuzinger (17-9) Friday. 
</P>
<P>
St. Anthony lost to Leuzinger, 65-58, and finished the season 15-6. Jordan 
(10-16) lost to St. Monica, 65-58, and El Rancho (15-9) lost to Alhambra, 
57-43. 
</P>
<P>
In 5-A, Cerritos (21-5) won at Esperanza, 75-69, as Mark Flick scored 19 points 
and Scott Day scored 18. The Dons will play host to No. 1 Mater Dei (26-1) 
Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
In 4-AA, top-ranked Dominguez (20-5) defeated St. John Bosco, 65-46. Michael 
Whittiker scored 13 points for the Dons, who play host to Rosemead (14-9) in 
the second round. Bosco finished 9-16. 
</P>
<P>
Second-seeded Compton, with Curtis Thomas scoring 29 points, downed Torrance, 
99-91, to move into the second round for a home game against California. The 
Tarbabes are 19-6. 
</P>
<P>
California (18-6) edged Gahr, 72-71, on a jump shot by Paul White with five 
seconds to play. Whittier (19-6) beat Arlington, 79-56, and will play at Bishop 
Amat (15-11) in the second round. 
</P>
<P>
In 4-A, top-ranked Artesia (21-2), which did not play Tuesday, will play host 
to La Puente (13-11) in the second round. 
</P>
<P>
La Mirada (17-8) defeated Santa Fe, 74-71, behind Brian Tiller's 17 points. The 
Matadors advance to a second-round game at home against Palm Desert (12-11). 
</P>
<P>
Poor shooting hurt Norwalk as the Lancers (10-14) lost to Bishop Montgomery, 
68-50. 
</P>
<P>
In 3-AA, Centennial beat Savanna, 60-53. The Apaches, who got 15 points from 
Charles Newman, will play at Foothill (18-6) Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Glenn lost to Rolling Hills, 100-72, and finished 5-17. 
</P>
<P>
In 3-A, St. Paul, led by Edgar Diaz's 21 points, defeated Costa Mesa, 85-79. 
The Swordsmen (7-15) will play at Corona del Mar (16-9). 
</P>
<P>
Bellflower (9-13) lost at home to South Pasadena, 59-45. 
</P>
<P>
Mayfair finished the season 0-23 with a 90-45 loss at St. Bernard. 
</P>
<P>
In 2-AA, Pius X (3-18) rolled past Salesian, 104-69, and will play at Santa 
Clara (20-0). Rod Titus scored 25 points for the Warriors. 
</P>
<P>
In 2-A, Cantwell (13-9) defeated Oak Park, 59-51, and will play at Valley 
Christian (19-5). 
</P>
<P>
In 1-A, Brethren (16-8) broke Hesperia Christian's 80-game home winning streak 
with a 65-52 victory. Chris Beck scored 18 for Brethren, which will play host 
to Bishop Diego (15-8). 
</P>
<P>
And in Small Schools, Gethsemane Baptist of Long Beach lost to Avalon, 71-45, 
and finished 14-6. 
</P>
</TEXT>
