<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: OCCIDENTAL TO HOST COLD WAR CONFERENCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cold War and recent political upheaval in Europe will be the focus of a 
two-day gathering of political commentators and students beginning Friday at 
Occidental College. 
</P>
<P>
Titled "Is the Cold War Over?: The International System into the Nineties," the 
first Occidental Public Affairs Conference will feature a series of workshops 
and panel discussions. 
</P>
<P>
Among the speakers will be Rep. Patricia Schroeder (D-Colorado); William 
Maynes, editor of Foreign Policy magazine; Washington Post journalist Jay 
Matthews; Sergei Plekhanov, deputy director of the Institute of U.S. and 
Canadian Studies of the U.S.S.R. Academy of Sciences, Moscow; and Robert 
Kuttner, author of "The Economic Illusion" and a contributing editor of the New 
Republic. 
</P>
<P>
Funded by the Ford Foundation, the conference was conceived and organized by 
two senior public policy majors at the college. The planners hope it will 
become an annual event, spurring greater student involvement in current issues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
