<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: AGENCY SEEKS PROPOSALS TO REDEVELOP BLOCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Glendale Redevelopment Agency on Tuesday initiated plans to develop another 
major office, retail and plaza complex in the high-rise business district on 
North Brand Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
Within a few days, the agency will send notices to owners of all property on 
the east side of the 400 block of North Brand Boulevard, inviting suggestions 
and proposals for redevelopment. 
</P>
<P>
All property owners within the block are eligible to participate, provided 
their proposals meet requirements adopted by the agency Tuesday, said Jeanne 
Armstrong, redevelopment director. 
</P>
<P>
A single project should be proposed for the entire block, bounded by Brand, 
Milford Street, Maryland Avenue and Lexington Drive. Use of the existing 
structures or construction of an entirely new complex will be considered. 
</P>
<P>
The block includes the main office of Valley National Bank, one of the first 
medium-rise structures built several decades ago to replace the original 
Midwest-style brick storefronts that then lined the boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
The agency's design consultants have recommended that the development 
incorporate high-rise office towers at the corners of the block with retail 
stores, a public plaza and at least one major restaurant. A multilevel parking 
garage also would be included. 
</P>
<P>
Property owners have until the end of March to submit proposals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
