<HEADLINE>
<P>
WATER METER FOR EACH APARTMENT OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In an effort to promote water conservation, the Santa Monica City Council 
approved an ordinance requiring all new apartment units to have individual 
water meters -- which will mean individual water bills. 
</P>
<P>
"The object of this measure is to create individual accountability," said Mayor 
Dennis Zane. 
</P>
<P>
The individual meters will add about $800 per unit to the cost of building an 
average apartment structure, officials estimate. Affordable-housing 
developments will be exempt from the ordinance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
