<HEADLINE>
<P>
SORTING OF CURBSIDE TRASH RECOMMENDED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beverly Hills residents would sort their trash for curbside collection under a 
recycling program recommended by a citizens' committee to the City Council at 
its regular meeting Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
The committee also called for a program to recycle grass cuttings and other 
garden trash. 
</P>
<P>
The report was the first step toward drawing up a solid-waste management plan 
required under state law. 
</P>
<P>
The city is obligated to submit its plan and have it approved by the county no 
later than July, 1991. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA021590-0109 </DOCNO>
