<HEADLINE>
<P>
CSUN'S PILE QUALIFIES FOR TRIPLE JUMP EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lolita Pile of Cal State Northridge jumped 40 feet 3 inches in the triple jump 
at an all-comers meet at CSUN on Saturday to qualify for the NCAA Division II 
championships. 
</P>
<P>
The school record-holder in the triple jump (42-4 3/4), Pile placed second in 
the Division II meet last year, fourth in '88 and eighth in '87. 
</P>
</TEXT>
