NEVADA LAS VEGAS LACKING DEPTH FOR NEW MEXICO STATE SHOWDOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DICK WAGNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAS VEGAS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Seventh-ranked Nevada Las Vegas faces 25th-ranked New Mexico State in a Big 
West Conference showdown tonight, but the Rebels are not in good shape. 
</P>
<P>
Starting guard Greg Anthony is out with a broken jaw for UNLV (20-4, 12-1), 
reserve guard Stacey Cvijanovich has a separated shoulder and reserve guard 
Travis Bice has the chicken pox. 
</P>
<P>
The Aggies (20-2, 11-1) defeated the Rebels, 83-82, in Las Cruces on Jan. 14, 
their first victory in the 15-game series. Guards Randy Brown and Keith Hill 
combined for 46 points in that game. 
</P>
