<TEXT>
<P>
Boeing Predicts Deal With China: Boeing Commercial Airplanes President Dean 
Thornton predicted that Boeing will clinch a deal with China to build 150 
aircraft by year-end. 
</P>
<P>
Thornton made his comments at the Asian Aerospace 90 air show in Singapore. 
China has already built 13 MD-82s in cooperation with McDonnell Douglas in a 
program to construct 25 aircraft. China is considered likely to insist on 
participating in the project to design and build either Boeing 737-300s or 
McDonnell Douglas' MD-90s. 
</P>
