<HEADLINE>
<P>
PROTEST OVER WAR TOYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The battle against war toys on Wednesday moved to an auto wrecking company on 
East 92nd Street in Los Angeles, where thousands of play guns were crushed. 
</P>
<P>
The demolition, sponsored by the Los Angeles Alliance for Survival, was billed 
as a "teach love, not war" effort aimed at preaching that "war is not a game." 
</P>
<P>
Alliance members planned to gift-wrap a solid block formed by the crushed toys 
and send it to the Toy Manufacturers of America during the 21st annual Toy Fair 
now under way in New York City. 
</P>
</TEXT>
