<P>
METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: WITNESSES TO FATAL FREEWAY ACCIDENT SOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police sought public assistance Wednesday in investigating the death of a 
34-year-old motorist on the Harbor Freeway near downtown Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
The man was killed when an unknown object smashed through the windshield of his 
van and struck him in the forehead. 
</P>
<P>
Lt. Bruce Hagerty said investigators hope to determine whether John A. Raff of 
Los Angeles, a self-employed glass architect, was killed by something thrown 
from an overpass or struck by an object accidentally hurled up from the 
roadway. 
</P>
<P>
Hagerty urged motorists and pedestrians who may have witnessed the incident, 
which occurred about 1:15 p.m. Tuesday near freeway overpasses at 23rd Street 
or Adams Boulevard, to call detectives at (213) 237-1733 or (213) 237-1774. 
</P>
