Newport Beach. Fierce winds drove most of the remaining slick onto Orange 
County beaches. ; Photo, Workers scoop up to four inches of oil off Newport 
Beach. The goo is packed into plastic bags, below. KEN HIVELY/ / Los Angeles 
Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
