<P>
76ER BARKLEY IN EARRING THRONG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PHILADELPHIA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Charles Barkley doesn't have an NBA championship ring on his finger, but he 
does have a winning streak ring on his ear. 
</P>
<P>
Barkley showed up in the Philadelphia 76ers locker room Wednesday night wearing 
a diamond-studded earring on his left ear, similar to those worn by Mike 
Gminski and Rick Mahorn as a result of a pact among several members on the team 
to get their ears pierced if they won 10 straight games 
</P>
<P>
They won 12 straight before losing two last week. 
</P>
<P>
"I said when I was ready to do it, I'd do it," he said. "We made a pact, and 
I'm going to stick to it. It's a permanent fixture." 
</P>
<P>
According to Gminski, once the team accomplished the 10-game goal, Barkley had 
talked Mahorn and Gminski into joining him on the earring promise. 
</P>
<P>
"I think once he saw Rick and I had done it, he finally succumbed to peer-group 
pressure," Gminski said. "He was, like, back there making the snowballs and we 
were throwing them, and so he had to finally step up to the plate." 
</P>
</TEXT>
